AUDIO: 'As we look back in history, every technological revolution started with new hardware and then was made widespread by an operating system. For the PC revolution, it was Windows and Mac OS. For the internet, it was'

[00:14] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'networking protocols and the web browser. For mobile, it was iOS and Android. It is the operating system agnostic to both hardware underneath and applications above which defines these'

[00:26] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'revolutions and creates the most value by democratizing new hardware and application adoption. AI will dwarf all of the previous computing ages in both size and'

[00:39] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'velocity. In the 70s, only computer scientists could operate a computer. With Windows, everyone could. Today we are at that same inflection point with'

[00:52] [scene:talk]
